<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1099> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1099" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. ([- - - -] Gallus; Fabius' name entire); Plin. NH 33.44; Eutrop. 2.16; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd. (Gallo Sabino et Pisone); Chr. Pasc.; Zon. 8.7; Degrassi, 40f., 114, 432f. Both Consuls campaigned in Bruttium against a Samnite brigand, Lollius (Zon. 8.7; cf. Dion. Hal. 20.17). Pliny places the beginning of the silver coinage in this consulship (33.44; cf. Jerome, Chr. ad ann. 271, p. 130 Helm). A revolt in Picenum remained for their successors to quell (Eutrop. 2.16)." .
